Simplify how opcodes in the modrm byte, and registers embedded in the opcode
are represented. Instead of creating a hidden operand (which must be programmed
around), just add it to open space in the array holding the opcode byte
sequence.

Note: Tests are done by verifying the model is unchanged, and the
operand indices in ncdis_iter_test.internal only changes operand references
to reflect no hidden operands.

